  <div class="section" id="module-pyjld.system.daemon.base">
<h1>Welcome to <em>pyjld.system</em> documentation!<a class="headerlink" href="#module-pyjld.system.daemon.base" title="Permalink to this headline">¶</a></h1>
<p>pyjld.system: various system level utilities (e.g. daemon)</p>
<p>This package contains various system level utilities.</p>
<p>&#64;author: Jean-Lou Dupont</p>
<p><tt class="xref docutils literal"><span class="pre">pyjld.system.daemon</span></tt></p>
<p>This module borrows heavily from <a class="reference external" href="http://pypi.python.org/pypi/python-daemon/">python_daemon</a> available at Pypi</p>
<dl class="class">
<dt id="pyjld.system.daemon.base.DaemonRunner">
<!--[pyjld.system.daemon.base.DaemonRunner]-->class <tt class="descclassname">pyjld.system.daemon.base.</tt><tt class="descname">DaemonRunner</tt><big>(</big><em>app</em><big>)</big><a class="headerlink" href="#pyjld.system.daemon.base.DaemonRunner" title="Permalink to this definition">¶</a></dt>
<dd><p>Controller class for a callable running in a separate background process</p>
<p>The principal methods are:</p>
<ul class="simple">
<li><a title="pyjld.system.daemon.base.DaemonRunner.cmd_start" class="reference internal" href="#pyjld.system.daemon.base.DaemonRunner.cmd_start"><tt class="xref docutils literal"><span class="pre">cmd_start()</span></tt></a></li>
<li><a title="pyjld.system.daemon.base.DaemonRunner.cmd_stop" class="reference internal" href="#pyjld.system.daemon.base.DaemonRunner.cmd_stop"><tt class="xref docutils literal"><span class="pre">cmd_stop()</span></tt></a></li>
</ul>
<p>The <tt class="docutils literal"><span class="pre">PID</span> <span class="pre">lock</span> <span class="pre">file</span></tt> is derived from <tt class="docutils literal"><span class="pre">app.name</span></tt> in the following way</p>
<pre>${app.pid_directory}/${app.name}.pid</pre>
<p>and by default is located in the <tt class="docutils literal"><span class="pre">/var/run</span></tt> directory; this directory
can be customized through the <tt class="docutils literal"><span class="pre">app.pid_directory</span></tt> attribute.</p>
<p>The exceptions generated by this class contain <cite>pseudo-messages</cite> which are
really meant as <cite>index</cite> to human readable messages. This way, customization
is easier to handle.</p>
<p><strong>Exceptions raised</strong></p>
<p>All exceptions specific to this class are raised with <a title="pyjld.system.daemon.base.DaemonRunnerException" class="reference internal" href="#pyjld.system.daemon.base.DaemonRunnerException"><tt class="xref docutils literal"><span class="pre">DaemonRunnerException</span></tt></a>
and the following <em>message identifiers</em> are defined:</p>
<blockquote>
<ul class="simple">
<li>error_pidfile_locked</li>
<li>error_daemon_aborted</li>
<li>error_daemon_open</li>
<li>error_daemon_terminate_process</li>
<li>error_daemon_openfilepath</li>
<li>error_application_method_not_found</li>
</ul>
</blockquote>
<p>The parameter <tt class="docutils literal"><span class="pre">app</span></tt> must be a callable with, as minimum, the following attributes:</p>
<ul class="simple">
<li><em>name</em></li>
<li><em>run()</em> method</li>
<li><em>exit()</em> method</li>
</ul>
<p>Optional attributes are:</p>
<ul class="simple">
<li><em>before_start()</em> method</li>
<li><em>before_run()</em> method</li>
</ul>
<p>The <tt class="xref docutils literal"><span class="pre">exit()</span></tt> is called when the daemon is shutting down eg. it received
a SIGTERM signal ( called also during the <a title="pyjld.system.daemon.base.DaemonRunner.cmd_stop" class="reference internal" href="#pyjld.system.daemon.base.DaemonRunner.cmd_stop"><tt class="xref docutils literal"><span class="pre">cmd_stop()</span></tt></a> ).</p>
<dl class="method">
<dt id="pyjld.system.daemon.base.DaemonRunner.cmd_restart">
<!--[pyjld.system.daemon.base.DaemonRunner.cmd_restart]--><tt class="descname">cmd_restart</tt><big>(</big><big>)</big><a class="headerlink" href="#pyjld.system.daemon.base.DaemonRunner.cmd_restart" title="Permalink to this definition">¶</a></dt>
<dd>Restarts the daemon for (the currently running) <tt class="docutils literal"><span class="pre">app</span></tt></dd></dl>

<dl class="method">
<dt id="pyjld.system.daemon.base.DaemonRunner.cmd_start">
<!--[pyjld.system.daemon.base.DaemonRunner.cmd_start]--><tt class="descname">cmd_start</tt><big>(</big><big>)</big><a class="headerlink" href="#pyjld.system.daemon.base.DaemonRunner.cmd_start" title="Permalink to this definition">¶</a></dt>
<dd><p>Starts the daemon for <tt class="docutils literal"><span class="pre">app</span></tt></p>
<p>The method <tt class="xref docutils literal"><span class="pre">app.before_start()</span></tt> is called prior to actually daemonizing;
the method can abort the process by raising ...</p>
<p>The method <tt class="xref docutils literal"><span class="pre">app.before_start()</span></tt> need not to exist (a validity check is performed).</p>
</dd></dl>

<dl class="method">
<dt id="pyjld.system.daemon.base.DaemonRunner.cmd_stop">
<!--[pyjld.system.daemon.base.DaemonRunner.cmd_stop]--><tt class="descname">cmd_stop</tt><big>(</big><big>)</big><a class="headerlink" href="#pyjld.system.daemon.base.DaemonRunner.cmd_stop" title="Permalink to this definition">¶</a></dt>
<dd>Stops the daemon for (the currently running) <tt class="docutils literal"><span class="pre">app</span></tt> but not before calling <tt class="docutils literal"><span class="pre">app.stop</span></tt></dd></dl>

</dd></dl>

<dl class="exception">
<dt id="pyjld.system.daemon.base.DaemonRunnerException">
<!--[pyjld.system.daemon.base.DaemonRunnerException]-->exception <tt class="descclassname">pyjld.system.daemon.base.</tt><tt class="descname">DaemonRunnerException</tt><a class="headerlink" href="#pyjld.system.daemon.base.DaemonRunnerException" title="Permalink to this definition">¶</a></dt>
<dd><p>DaemonRunner Exception base class</p>
<p>Allows for easier customization of error messages.
Use <cite>duck typing</cite> to inspect the Exception for the 
<tt class="xref docutils literal"><span class="pre">msg_id</span></tt> &amp; <tt class="xref docutils literal"><span class="pre">params</span></tt> attributes.</p>
</dd></dl>

<dl class="class">
<dt id="pyjld.system.daemon.base.ReferenceApp">
<!--[pyjld.system.daemon.base.ReferenceApp]-->class <tt class="descclassname">pyjld.system.daemon.base.</tt><tt class="descname">ReferenceApp</tt><a class="headerlink" href="#pyjld.system.daemon.base.ReferenceApp" title="Permalink to this definition">¶</a></dt>
<dd><p>Used as model of an <tt class="docutils literal"><span class="pre">app</span></tt></p>
<dl class="attribute">
<dt id="pyjld.system.daemon.base.ReferenceApp.requiredAttributes">
<!--[pyjld.system.daemon.base.ReferenceApp.requiredAttributes]--><tt class="descname">requiredAttributes</tt><a class="headerlink" href="#pyjld.system.daemon.base.ReferenceApp.requiredAttributes" title="Permalink to this definition">¶</a></dt>
<dd>Generates the list of required attributes</dd></dl>

</dd></dl>

